ğŸ§  What is TDZ â€“ Temporal Dead Zone?

Temporal Dead Zone means â€”
a period of time during code execution
when a variable exists in memory,
but cannot be accessed or used yet ğŸ˜µ

ğŸ”¹ Step-by-Step Explanation
Example:
